title: Hope cheerleaders wear pink to support Breast Cancer Awareness
text: Hope cheerleaders wear pink to support Breast Cancer Awareness Hope Bobcat and Bobkitten senior and junior high cheerleaders continue their years of tradition to cheer in pink for the month of October in support of Breast Cancer Awareness month. Comment Posted Oct. 15, 2015 at 7:00 AM Hope, Ark. Hope Bobcat and Bobkitten senior and junior high cheerleaders continue their years of tradition to cheer in pink for the month of October in support of Breast Cancer Awareness month. They've brought the spirit to the atmosphere for the fans during football action this season and pinked out Hammons Stadium last week. The Bobcat and Bobkitten cheerleaders will continue wearing pink cheer attire for this month during football season.
